# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback.
#
# React Router (BrowserRouter) handles client-side navigation, but when a
# user pastes a URL like https://ptowl.com/dashboard directly into the
# browser, refreshes on a deep route, or follows an external link, the
# request hits CF Pages BEFORE React Router exists. CF looks for a real
# file at /dashboard, doesn't find one, and 404s.
#
# This rule says: for ANY path (`/*`) where no real file exists, serve
# index.html with a 200 status. The browser then loads the SPA, React
# Router parses the URL, and the right page renders.
#
# Without this, /dashboard, /about, /privacy, /terms, /security, /profile,
# /customize/templates, /customize/print, and /schedule/:id would all
# 404 on direct access.
#
# CF Pages uses this only when no static asset matches. Real assets like
# /assets/foo.js, /favicon.svg, /logo.svg etc. continue to serve normally.

/*    /index.html   200
